The '''Aapua wind park''' ({{lang-sv|'''Aapua-parken'''}}) is a [[wind park]] on Eta, southwest of [[Aapua]], [[Övertorneå municipality]] in [[Norrbotten County]], [[Sweden]]. {{As of|2007}}, it is the northern-most wind park in Sweden.<ref name="dn_hetvindkraft">{{cite news | first1 = Ole | last1 = Rothberg | authorlink = | author2 =Andersson, Mikael | title = Het vindkraft sätter snurr på det gamla varvet | url = http://www.dn.se/DNet/jsp/polopoly.jsp?d=678&a=727385 | format = | work = Dagens nyheter | publisher = | location = Stockholm | id = | pages = | page = | date = 2007-12-22 | accessdate = 2008-01-03 | language = Swedish | quote = | archiveurl =https://archive.is/20070815051409/http://www.dn.se/DNet/jsp/polopoly.jsp?d=678&a=727385 | dead-url = yes | archivedate =2007-08-15 }}</ref> The park is owned by '''Aapua Vind AB''', representing 14 private investors, and operates on land owned by the state-owned [[Sveaskog]], Sweden's largest forest owner.<ref name="nyteknik20070925">{{cite web|url=http://www.nyteknik.se/nyheter/energi_miljo/vindkraft/article45715.ece |title=Rusning till Sveaskog efter bra vindkraftlägen - Ny Teknik |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110608060145/http://www.nyteknik.se/nyheter/energi_miljo/vindkraft/article45715.ece |archivedate=2011-06-08 }}</ref> The plant came online in 2005<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.avanza.se/aza/press/news.jsp?n=675834|title=Placera Nu Sveaskog: Medvind för vindkraft i skogsmiljö<!-- Bot generated title -->}}</ref>
==Technical== The park consists of seven 1.5 MW [[Vestas]] [[Vestas V82|V82-1.5 MW Arctic]] [[wind turbine]]s<ref name="vestasbrochure">{{cite web|url=http://www.vestas.com/Admin/Public/DWSDownload.aspx?File=%2FFiles%2FFiler%2FSE%2FBrochures%2FAapua_SE.pdf |archive-url=http://arquivo.pt/wayback/20090706142444/http://www.vestas.com/Admin/Public/DWSDownload.aspx?File=%2fFiles%2fFiler%2fSE%2fBrochures%2fAapua_SE.pdf |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2009-07-06 |title=www.vestas.com/Admin/Public/DWSDownload.aspx?File=%2FFiles%2FFiler%2FSE%2FBrochures%2FAapua_SE.pdf |format=PDF }}</ref> with a total stated power of 9.9 MW<ref name="nyteknik20070925"/> (10.5 MW according to supplier Vestas<ref name="vestasbrochure" />). Each unit has a nacelle height of 78&nbsp;m and a rotor diameter of 82&nbsp;m.<ref name="vestasbrochure" />
