{{primary sources|date=August 2012}} {{Infobox company | name = Lee Valley Tools Ltd. | logo = Lee Valley.JPG | logo_size = 250px | type = Private | genre = | foundation = [[Ottawa]], [[Ontario]], [[Canada]] (1978) | founder = [[Leonard Lee]] | location_city = [[Ottawa]], [[Ontario]] | location_country = [[Canada]] | location = | locations = 18 | area_served = Canada | key_people = | industry = Tools | products = Woodworking and Gardening Tools | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | slogan = | homepage = http://www.leevalley.com/ | footnotes = | intl = }}
'''Lee Valley Tools Ltd.''' is a [[Canada|Canadian]] business specializing in tools and gifts for woodworking and gardening.
==Corporate identity== The company is family-owned. The founder, [[Leonard Lee]], was a recipient of the [[Order of Canada]]. He founded the company in 1978, in [[Ottawa]], [[Ontario]]. Over the next ten years, the company opened several more stores (Toronto, Vancouver) and started manufacturing its own line of tools (starting with the Veritas Dovetail Marker in 1982). Since then, it has continued opening stores, manufacturing more diverse tools, and selling through mail order and the Internet. In 1998, Canica Design was launched. Canica is a medical design company associated with Lee Valley Tools<ref>http://www.leevalley.com/en/home/contact.aspx</ref> which arose out of consultations between Leonard Lee and surgeon Michael Bell after Lee found that Bell was using Lee Valley tools in his plastic surgery practice.
==Consumer sales== The primary business is [[Mail order|mail-order]] and retail, purveying mainly [[woodworking]] and [[gardening]] tools and equipment, as well as woodworking hardware and gifts. The consumer part of the business runs under the main company name, Lee Valley Tools.
==Veritas Tools== Lee Valley also has a manufacturing arm, called '''Veritas Tools'''. Veritas makes many woodworking hand-tools, including [[hand plane]]s, [[marking gauge]]s and other measuring tools, [[wood router|router]] tables, sharpening systems, and numerous other gadgets. Veritas does research and development activities for the factory line, and has developed and patented many innovative designs.
